    <item>
      <title>Repair &amp; Refinement</title>
      <link>https://zuluhotelomega.com/infovault/misc/repairandrefinement/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 17 Nov 2024 11:47:31 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>https://zuluhotelomega.com/infovault/misc/repairandrefinement/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;how-does-repair--refinement-work&#34;&gt;How does repair &amp;amp; refinement work?&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You will need to make sure you’ve got these things:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;1 : a retort tool (can be bought from the vanity shop)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;2 : required reagents (see the table below)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;repairing&#34;&gt;Repairing:&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To repair an item without the help from a Crafter, you will need to apply mending oil.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Mending Oil will take on the quality of the material used and use it to repair any piece of equipment.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
